name: Frida Punk 041 - You got a friend in me
description:
Fun fact: Frida was a close friend of American artist Georgia O'Keeffe
The two painters met in December 1931, at the opening of Diego Rivera's big solo exhibition at New York's Museum of Modern Art. According to one of Rivera's assistants, the famed muralist had later bragged that his wife had been flirting with O'Keeffe. The two continued to correspond for some time after as Frida would send letters to Georgia.
